  <!-- Guide page -->
  <data name="GuideTitle.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Guide</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideWhatItDoesTitle.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>What it does</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideWhatItDoes.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>gdriveHandler registers itself as the default opener for Google Workspace shortcut files (.gdoc, .gsheet, .gslides, and more). When you open one of these files, it reads the email address stored inside the file, finds the Chrome or Edge profile signed in with that account, and launches the document in the right profile — so you always land in the right account instead of seeing "You need access."</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideSupportedFilesTitle.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Supported files</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideHowMatchingTitle.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>How it finds the right profile</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideHowMatching.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>1. Reads the email address from the shortcut file.
2. Checks every Chrome and Edge profile for one signed in with that exact email.
3. If a match is found, opens the file in that profile.
4. If no direct match, checks your Aliases table — if the email is mapped to another address, tries again with the mapped address.
5. If still no match, opens in Chrome's active profile (or your system default browser if Chrome is not installed).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideOpenRightAccountTitle.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Open the right account — aliases</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideOpenRightAccount.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>If a shortcut file was created with an old email address (for example after switching from a personal Gmail to a work account), add an alias on the Aliases page:

  From: old@gmail.com
  To:   current@company.com

gdriveHandler will then route files with the old address to your current profile.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideEdgeNoteTitle.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Edge note</value>
  </data>
  <data name="GuideEdgeNote.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Chrome profiles are matched by Google account email — reliable. Edge profiles are matched by Microsoft account. A Google account used in an Edge browser session is only matched when it is the Edge profile's primary signed-in identity. If Edge causes wrong matches, you can disable it in Settings.</value>
  </data>
